    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Frames with a profusion of overlapping and intertwining scrolls and volutes, popular during the 16th and 17th centuries and named for Venetian architect and sculptor Jacopo Sansovino.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para marcos con una profusión de espirales y volutas sobrepuestas y entrelazadas, popular durante los siglos XVI y XVII y que llevan el nombre del escultor y arquitecto veneciano Jacopo Sansovino.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor lijsten met veel overlappende en ineengestrengelde krullen en spiralen. Ze waren populair tijdens de 16e en 17e eeuw en zijn vernoemd naar de Venetiaanse architect en beeldhouwer Jacopo Sansovino.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>卷飾及渦紋大量交疊穿插的框架，在十六和十七世紀廣受歡迎，以義大利威尼斯建築師兼雕刻家賈柯波．桑索維諾（Jacopo Sansovino）命名。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ein Rahmen mit einer Fülle von einander überlappenden und ineinandergreifenden Rollwerkelementen und Voluten, beliebt im 16. und 17. Jahrhundert und benannt nach dem venezianischen Architekten und Bildhauer Jacopo Sansovino.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
